column5: awesome ski ben congrats
That's too bad John.  Lets try and work something out for next year.
Way to go Ben! You must have been pumped oh that one! Congrats on the great fish.
Awesome job Ben That is a true beauty Leechman
Nice fish Ben.Sure is nice when thing come together. I see you still need a dream boat.
Holy Crikey Bennie!!!  That's a Beauty.  And still so much season left to take an even bigger one if ya want.
This fish inhaled a top raider in a weedy nook along a major currant area.  What a thrill!!  49" of Lac Seul adrenalin!            Yesterday I saw 2 different fish that were much bigger
SWEET nice job man,lucky fellar living up there
Ben that's amazing, congrat's bud!
Nice one, all smiles in those pic's, WTG...
The smile says it all
Beautiful.  Congrats Ben
Sweet one, looks like the dirty weather is paying off for the musky guys.
Must have been awesome to get that fish on topwater! Big one, good job.
Even having had my first muskie grabs this summer, I can't imagine what it must be like to actually hook and land one of those monsters. Wow! Is all I can say. Jim
Nice fish ! WOOO
49r on top water, wow!!  Congrats.
Love the shoulders! chunky!!  great waters there, anyone see pictures of Linda Rice? GIANTS
I throw my TopRaider all the time hoping for a blowup like the one I'm sure you had  Good job man!!!

I've seen them all.     I guide for the lodge that Linda owns (Moosehorn).  She's a great muskie angler and dedicates a lot of time to chasing them.  Her biggest this year is a 54.5" and her fishing partner boated a 56 1/4" monster last week.    Between them they have 10 over 50" this year alone.
WTG Ben....thats a monster. Like someone else said , the smile says it all....if it were me i'd still be grinning now....lol!!!  PS...thanks for the sneak preview.
Oh that is nice!
sweet fish Ben!!
Awesome fish.... Keep em coming!
Wow, that's a nice fish there Ben!  Well done man.
beauty fish.
sexy!  The fish that is...
Beauty! Sure wish we had those out west here. Wish I could have made it down this summer for some fishing but work has been busy.
nice fish Ben  Now I have to add another lake to the upcoming NW trip ! Don't think I will have enough time LOL  TB
awesome fish ben congrats
